### English Title:
The Crisis of Egyptian Doctors' Migration Intensifies

### English Text Summary:
The migration crisis of Egyptian doctors has escalated significantly, prompting parliamentary calls for strict regulations that would require them to work in the country for five years before considering emigration. This issue has sparked widespread debate, intensified by statements from Egyptian Prime Minister Mustafa, who noted that the migration of doctors abroad generates financial and economic returns for Egypt and is part of the state's policy. He also mentioned a vision to double the number of medical graduates due to increasing demand. Daily episodes of the program can be watched at 3 PM GMT from Monday to Friday, with trending stories available through a provided link.

